org.apache.cassandra.thrift

Class ColumnSlice

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.cassandra.thrift.ColumnSlice
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ColumnSlice>, org.apache.thrift.TBase<ColumnSlice,ColumnSlice._Fields>

    public class ColumnSlice
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.thrift.TBase<ColumnSlice,ColumnSlice._Fields>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ColumnSlice>
    The ColumnSlice is used to select a set of columns from inside a row. If start or finish are unspecified they will default to the start-of end-of value.
    See Also:
